						<div class="postbody">In a MAP editor, you'd need to only edit a map at time. Then save it in a .sav file, to rename it manually into a .bin file to include in a larger NES ROM. Scince the goal is to get the result in a larger ROM, I think metatiles doesn't have to suffer of stupid restrictions.
<br />Simply encode all metatiles sets for a standard game plus a map editor in 16kb is decent.</div>

					
